					<div class="comment-body">
						
                            
							<blockquote><p>We need a system where health staff are accountable to standards, not their employers.</p><p>This is root and branch of the problem.</p><p>Whistleblowing should be anonymous, logged somewhere outside the employing body's purview and investigated by independent reviewers (with peer input).</p><p>Otherwise it's not whistleblowing but russian roulette for the staff.</p></blockquote><p>Why focus on the health staff?  It is the management (brought in from the private sector) that have put medics in intolerable positions. They cannot complain or strike. Consequently they have to put up with all the carp in terms of impossible and conflicting polices, targets and procedures while the patients (or more commonly, patients relatives) attack them and look for reasons to sue due to relentless anti public-sector media items.</p><p>I am all for whistle blowing though. However, the public will not want to pay to make the wards properly staffed and equipped. That is the bottom line.</p>
						
